http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/bangalore/Vehicles-gutted/article13986339.ece

A car and five motorcycles, including a Harley Davidson, parked on the ground floor of a house in Marathahalli were gutted due to suspected electric shortcircuit in the wee hours of Thursday.The inmates of the house woke up when thick smoke engulfed the house and rushed out to notice that the vehicles were charred. Even the front portion of the house was burnt.Though the HAL police suspect that electric shortcircuit could be the reason behind the fire, the police are further investigating to ascertain the exact reason for the mishap.